			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>So I&#8217;ve discovered since I started this sky watch thing&#8230; well&#8230; I have really been watching the sky a lot more.  Have you done that lately?  I mean, just look at the sky.  Its really quite amazing.  Many times the soft floating clouds appear to be a water color print painted on the horizon by God.  You should try it.  This week.  Everyday simply take some time and enjoy the sky.</p>
<p>I have two sky pictures this week.  The first one was taken as my brother and I went out to my lot.  We are about to begin construction on my new home and I brought him out there to show him were the house will be, the well, the septic tank&#8230; that sort of thing&#8230;  When we walked down to the edge of the water I glanced up and was like&#8230; wow&#8230; what a great view&#8230;  that would make a good Sky Watch picture.   Sooo here it is.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/kindasouthern/2721802127/" title="The Property by kindasouthern, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3003/2721802127_8c254f818e.jpg" width="500" height="375" alt="The Property" /></a></p>
<p>This next one, I was driving down the road on the way to church Wednesday night, the sun was coming in and out from behind the clouds and when I stopped at a light, I decided to snap a shot from the drivers side window.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/kindasouthern/2722625478/" title="Driving down the road by kindasouthern, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3058/2722625478_19ee7ac895.jpg" width="500" height="375" alt="Driving down the road" /></a></p>
<p>Thats it for this week.  </p>
<p>This is part of a thing over 300 ppl a week take part in called <a href="http://skyley.blogspot.com/">Sky Watch Friday</a>.  Just click that link if you want to see the sky from places all over the world.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
