Rachelle sent a txt not long ago referencing 2 Peter, so I decided to [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I began my day with a cold shower&#8230; (Our water heater has decided to turn off for some reason during the night) Which in turn made my shower shorter than usual.  This brought me to a cup of coffee and the bible.</p>
<p>Rachelle sent a txt not long ago referencing 2 Peter, so I decided to begin there.  I&#8217;m reading through, nodding in agreement,  Basically, be sure of who you are in Christ, of your calling&#8230; strive to follow the spirit in your daily life and if you do these things&#8230; you will never fail.</p>
<p>And the proclamation of a Majestic God declaring Jesus as His son. Then it moves on to false prophets, false teachers, people who speak about truth and life but live in death, walking in the flesh rather than the spirit.  Woe to the one who turns the weak away from God.  Woe to the one who uses his power of influence and smooth talk to charm away the weak, the hurting. And woe to the one who once knew God, who claimed to know Jesus then later purposely turned away.</p>
<p>With thoughts of 2 Peter running through my mind I begin the drive to work.  Listening to a harp and bowl session from IHOP Kansas City.   Thoughts of what if I have become a false prophet, a false teacher&#8230;  What about the impure thoughts that run through my mind&#8230;  The constant pressing of the flesh into my thoughts&#8230;  Am I speaking truth and life and yet allowing a portion of my mind to live in death, in lust, in deception?</p>
<p>Forgive me Lord.  Became my prayer.<br />
Entering in to a time of prayer, seeking God, again crying out for his revelation.  For the revelation of Jesus.  The cd simply becoming one part of this moment with God.  Praying and singing, not simply echoing the words, but praying and singing, interacting with God.</p>
<p>His love filling the air around me, me responding in love.  I realize Im crying, and smiling, and singing, and simply worshiping God as I drive down the road.  Simply interacting with a divine moment.</p>
<p>I love God, I truly do</p>
<p>Sometimes he seems so far away.  So distant and silent.  Maybe I try too hard to hear Him, to sense and feel His presence.  Maybe I dont try often enough. Maybe its me, my life that is in the way, I dont know.  But this morning, I interacting with God.  Not just a prayer to him, not just a revelation from him, a conversation, a special moment that he reserved especially for me. </p>
<p>If you feel God moving close to you, dont run away.  Dont hide in your failings.  Dont allow thoughts of your shortcommings to interrupt.  Simply open your heart, allow his forgiveness in and enter in to a divine interaction with God.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
